# 🧩 Use Cases – Unified UML Diagram

## 🎯 Overview
This document defines the unified UML use case structure for the **Population Reporting System** within the company’s data management platform.

---

## 👤 Primary Actor
**Clerical Staff**  
Responsible for all report generation activities.

---

## 🗂 Use Cases by Category

### 🌍 Country Reports (C1–C6)
| ID | Use Case Description |
|----|-----------------------|
| **UC1** | Generate report for **all countries worldwide** (sorted largest → smallest population) |
| **UC2** | Generate report for **all countries in a continent** (sorted largest → smallest population) |
| **UC3** | Generate report for **all countries in a region** (sorted largest → smallest population) |
| **UC4** | Generate report for **Top N countries worldwide** (user provides N) |
| **UC5** | Generate report for **Top N countries in a continent** (user provides N) |
| **UC6** | Generate report for **Top N countries in a region** (user provides N) |

---

### 🏙 City Reports (D1–D4)
| ID | Use Case Description |
|----|-----------------------|
| **UC7** | Generate report for **all cities worldwide** (sorted largest → smallest population) |
| **UC8** | Generate report for **all cities in a continent** (sorted largest → smallest population) |
| **UC9** | Generate report for **all cities in a region** (sorted largest → smallest population) |
| **UC10** | Generate report for **all cities in a country** (sorted largest → smallest population) |

---

## 🔁 Relationships

### 🔹 Include Relationships (Common Functionality)
All use cases **include**:
- **Data Retrieval and Sorting**
- **Report Generation and Formatting**

### ⚠️ Extension Points (Error Handling)
| Error Type | Affected Use Cases |
|-------------|--------------------|
| **Data Access Error** | UC2, UC3, UC4, UC5, UC6, UC7, UC8, UC9, UC10 |
| **Invalid Input Error** | UC4, UC5, UC6 (where user provides N) |

---

## 🧱 System Boundary
**Population Reporting System**  
Contains all use cases within the **data management platform**.

---

## ✅ Preconditions
All use cases require:
- User **authentication and authorization**
- Access to **current, validated population data**
- Proper **system functionality**

---

## 🎯 Success Conditions
- Reports generated with **correct sorting** (largest → smallest)
- Data presented in **usable, structured format** for organizational needs

---

## ❌ Failed Conditions
- Data retrieval errors  
- Invalid user inputs  
- System access or functionality issues

---

